<title>UK: Ex-dividends take 2.460 points off FTSE on Monday.</title>
<headline>Ex-dividends take 2.460 points off FTSE on Monday.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following FTSE-100 stocks go ex-dividend on Monday and will take 2.460 points off the index at the start of trading.</p>
<p>						   DIVIDEND    INDEX</p>
<p>						   (PENCE)     EFFECT</p>
<p>  COMPANY				     Net   Gross    Gross</p>
<p> * BAA					 7.90   9.88     0.601</p>
<p> * Boots				    14.30  17.88     0.945</p>
<p> * Severn Trent		     (a) 26.00  32.50     0.667</p>
<p> * 3i					  5.70   7.13     0.246</p>
<p>(a) includes a second interim of 3.84p</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717</p>
